        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Lindon, or 27 miles south of Akron, moving southeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 40 mph, and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Anton and Lindon.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If a tornado is spotted seek shelter inside a sturdy building.</instruction>
